ECB Says Emergency Bank Borrowing Rose to Highest in Nine Months

-- B y   G a b i   T h e s i n g
-- 
2011-12-08T08:56:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/ecb-says-emergency-bank-borrowing-rose-to-highest-in-nine-months.html
The  European Central Bank  said it
lent banks in the euro area the most in emergency overnight
funds since March 1 as the region faces a looming credit crunch.  Financial institutions borrowed 9.4 billion euros ($12.6
billion) at the rate of 2 percent yesterday, the ECB said in a
statement today. Overnight deposits at the Frankfurt-based
central stayed at 324.5 billion euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
